   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. Merkatu-Ereduak"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Hurrengo paragrafoetan, merkatu-eredua zer den eta zertarako garatzen diren azalduko da, hauek garatzeko motibazioa justifikatuta gera dadin.\n",
    "\n",
    "(Notebook hauetan garatutako kodea _Solvable stochastic dealer models for financial markets_ (K. Yamada _et al._ ) artikuluko grafikak lortzeko helburuarekin idatzi da. )\n",
    "\n",
    "Termodinamikan, gas idealaren eredu mikroskopiko batetatik Boyle-Charles-en lege makroskopikoa gara genezake. Honek, azterpenaren ikuspuntutik, zer suposatzen du? Ondorio garrantzitsuak, eta hasiera batean konplexu edota aldagai-anitzetakoak diruditenak ateratzeko gai izan gaitezkeela sistema bere sinpletasun handienera eramanez, eta sinpletasun hortatik aztertuz. Betiere, noski, sinpletasun hortan lanean gaudela kontuan izanik.\n",
    "\n",
    "Era berean, merkatu eredu mikroskopiko sinple bat eraikitzea izango da atal honen helburua, ondorio empiriko nagusiagoak garatzeko gai izango den eredu mikroskopikoa. Merkatuaren portaera makroskopikoak, negoziatzaile mikroskopikoen ekintzekin lotuz, merkatuak kontrolatzeko bideak aurkitzea posible dela ikusiko dugu. Eta zeintzuk dira merkatu batean ager daitezkeen akatsak? Esaterako, merkatu burbuilak, edota _crack_ finantziarioak (erorketa finantziarioak).\n",
    "\n",
    "Merkatu ereduen ikerketari, bost era ezberdinetan ekin diezaiokegu. Kategoria hauen izenak ingelesez idatziko dira, itzulpen zuzenik ez baitago oraindik.\n",
    "\n",
    "- _Order driven_ merkatu ereduak (edo _double action_ ereduak).\n",
    "- _Fundamentalists vs chartists_ ereduak.\n",
    "- _Minority games_.\n",
    "- _Spin-based models_.\n",
    "- _Dealer Models_.\n",
    "\n",
    "Azken hauxe da hurrengo ataletan analizatuko dena.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1.1. A Eredua - Simulazio estatikoa\n",
    "\n",
    "Kontsidera bedi merkatu eredu sinpleena, bi merkatariz osatutakoa. Bi merkatari hauek, bakoitza bere aldetik, produktu jakin baten saltze- eta eroste-prezioak eskainiko dituzte. \n",
    "\n",
    "Eroste-prezioak edo eskaintza-prezioak ( _bid price_ ) adierazten du zein den merkatari batek erosteko zehazten duen prezio maximoa. Saltze-prezioak edo eskari-prezioak ( _ask price_ ), ordea, erakusten du zein den merkatari horrek aurkezten duen saltze prezio minimoa. Merkatari ororentzat, helburua mozkin bat lortzea denez, eskari-prezioa eskaintza-prezioa baino altuagoa izan beharko da, eta bi prezio hauen arteko diferentziari $L$ deituko diogu, zeina, eredu sinplifikatu hontan, konstantea izango den merkatari ororentzat.\n",
    "\n",
    "Honela, merkatari bakoitzaren batezbesteko prezioak ( _mid-price_ ), eskari- eta eskaintza-prezioen arteko batazbestekoa erakutsiko du:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$p_i(t)=\\frac{p_s(t)-p_e(t)}{2}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Non $p_s(t)$ saltze-prezioa (eskari-prezioa) den, eta $p_e(t)$ eroste-prezioa (eskaintza-prezioa). Saltze/Eroste erabiliko dira azpi-indizeetarako beraien egokitasunagatik: eskari/eskaintza-k azpi-indize bera izango lukete, eta erosoagoa da aurrekoa erabiltzea, nahiz eta, berez, zuzenagoak izan bigarren terminoak. \n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1.1. Transakzio-baldintza\n",
    "\n",
    "Bi merkatarik transakzio bat izan dezaten, halabeharrezkoa da bataren eroste-prezioa bestearen saltze-prezioarekin bat erotzea. Bestela esanda:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$|p_1(t)-p_2(t)|\\geq L$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Hau betetzen ez den bitartean, merkatarien prezioak (erdi-prezioei hemendik aurrera zuzenean _prezio_ deritzogu) hemen deskribatzen den era aleatorioan aldatuz joango dira:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$p_i(t+\\Delta t)=p_i(t)+cf_i(t),\\quad i=1,2,$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$f_i(t)=\\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -\\Delta p, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "non $f_i(t)$ $i$. merkatariari dagokion zarata aleatorioa den eta $c$ parametro konstante bat. Prezioa aldatzen den aldiune bakoitzeko, $p_1(t)$ eta $p_2(t)$-ren arteko distantzia egiaztatzen da. $L$ baino handiagoa edo berdina bada, horrek adieraziko luke merkatari baten eroste-prezioa bestearen saltze-prezioa baino handiagoa dela, eta hortaz, **transakzio bat gertatuko litzateke**. Kasu honetan, bolumen unitateko akordio bat gertatuko da, bi merkatarien erdi-prezioen batazbestean, momentu hortako merkatu-prezioa zehaztuko duena. Transakzioa gertatzerakoan, bi merkatarien prezioak merkatu-prezioari doitzen zaizkie. Honen berdinak izango dira, eta $p_1(t)$ eta $p_2(t)$ prezioek berriro beraien prozesu aleatorioei ekingo diote baldintza berriz bete arte.\n",
    "\n",
    "Azkenik, bi aldagai gehiago gelditzen dira definitzeko. \n",
    "\n",
    "- $P(n)$: merkatuko prezioa zein den ematen du n ( _tick_ denbora-unitatea) transakzio-aldiune bakoitzean.\n",
    "- $I(n)$: (n-1). eta n. transakzioen artean igaro den denbora-tartea zehazten du. \n",
    "\n",
    "Hurrengo kode zatietan merkatu-prezioak eta transakzio denbora-tarteak irudikatuko dira."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.1.2. Libreriak, Parametroak eta Aldagaien hasieratzea"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "# ----------- LIBRERIAK ------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "from matplotlib import rc                  # Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import datetime\n",
    "import matplotlib.mlab as mlab            # mlab modulua inportatu MATLABeko komandoak erabili ahal izateko\n",
    "from random import choice\n",
    "from random import seed\n",
    "plt.style.use('fivethirtyeight')\n",
    "\n",
    "# ----------- PARAMETROAK -----------------\n",
    "Delta_p = 0.01\n",
    "c = 0.01\n",
    "L = 0.01\n",
    "N = 5000                         # transakzio kopuru totala (guk nahibeste)\n",
    "f_i = [-Delta_p,Delta_p]         # i. negoziatzaileari dagokion ausazko zarata \n",
    "dt = Delta_p*Delta_p\n",
    "tick = 0\n",
    "denbora = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# ------------ ALDAGAIAK -------------------\n",
    "p1 = 100.25           # Hasieratze balio bat (edozein jarri diet) \n",
    "p2 = 100.25\n",
    "P_n = np.zeros([N])   # Merkatuko Prezioa\n",
    "I_n = np.zeros([N])   # (n-1) eta n. transakzioen arteko denbora-tartea\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# ------------ FUNTZIO LAGUNGARRIAK -------------------\n",
    "def normalizatu(data):                       # normalizazio hau egiten da bariantza unitarioa lortzeko (hau gabe ere egin daiteke)\n",
    "    return ((data)/np.sqrt(np.var(data)))\n",
    "\n",
    "def itzulkin_log(Pt,tau=1):                  # Denbora-serie baten itzulkin logaritmikoa bueltatuko digun funtzioa\n",
    "    return np.log(Pt[tau:])-np.log(Pt[0:-tau])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.1.3. Merkatu prezioen eta transakzio-denboren kalkulua"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Kodea exekutatzeko, beheko testu-zelda _Code_ zelda bezala exekutatu. Orain _Markdown_ zelda gisan dago, lana exekutatzean, prozesua bizkortzeko, testu-fitxategia erabili delako datuak berreskuratzeko."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(12345)\n",
    "   \n",
    "startTime = datetime.datetime.now() \n",
    "\n",
    "while tick<N:                             # Guk nahi izandako transakzio kopurura heltzen ez den bitartean\n",
    "\n",
    "    while np.absolute(p1-p2)<L:           # Transakzio baldintza betetzen ez den bitartean\n",
    "        p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i) # 1D-ko prezioen higidura-ekuazioak \n",
    "        p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)\n",
    "        denbora += 1\n",
    "    avg = (p1+p2)/2\n",
    "    p1, p2 = avg, avg\n",
    "    P_n[tick] = avg\n",
    "    I_n[tick] = denbora\n",
    "    tick +=1\n",
    "\n",
    "endTime = datetime.datetime.now()\n",
    "T_osoa = endTime-startTime\n",
    "print('Exekuzioko denbora: ', T_osoa)\n",
    "\n",
    "np.savetxt('A_Eredua.txt',np.transpose([I_n, P_n]))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.1.4. Merkatuen prezioak eta transakzio denbora-tarteak (tick-en menpe)"

    "# --------- DATUAK BERRESKURATU ----------------\n",
    "I_n,P_n=np.loadtxt('A_Eredua.txt',unpack=True)\n",
    "d_prezioa=normalizatu(itzulkin_log(P_n,1))         # Merkatuko prezioaren itzulkin logaritmikoaren kalkuloa\n",
    "I_n_norm = normalizatu((I_n[2:]-I_n[1:-1])*dt)             # 2. Pausutik hartu diferentzia, I_n[0]=0 baita\n",
    "\n",
    "# --------- DATUAK IRUDIKATU ----------------\n",
    "# Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "mpl.rc('xtick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "mpl.rc('ytick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "plt.rc('text', usetex=True)\n",
    "plt.rc('font', family='serif')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, [a_x,b_x,c_x] = plt.subplots(figsize=(17,6),ncols=3,dpi=200)\n",
    "a_x.plot(P_n[0:],label=\"$P(n)$\", lw=2, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "a_x.set_ylabel(r\"$P(n)$ Merkatu-prezioa\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "a_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (\\textit{tick}-etan)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "b_x.plot(I_n_norm, lw=2)\n",
    "b_x.set_ylabel(r\"$I(n)$  Transakzio-tartea\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "b_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (\\textit{tick}-etan)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "c_x.plot(d_prezioa, lw=2)\n",
    "c_x.set_ylabel(r\"$R(n)$ Itzulkin logaritmikoa\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "c_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (\\textit{tick}-etan)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "t_kop = \"Transakzio kopurua:\"+str(N)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(t_kop)\n",
    "fig.savefig('AEredua.png')"
   ]

    "### 1.1.6. Aldagai-aldaketa eginez, 2D-tako Random Walk Finantzarioa simulatzea"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Eredu sinpleena den hauxe hobeto ulertu ahal izateko, jo dezagun 2 dimentsiotako random walk batetara. Honetarako, aldagai aldagai-aldaketa bat egingo da. Alde batetik, prezioen arteko diferentzia:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$D(t)=p_1(t)-p_2(t)\\quad\\longrightarrow\\quad D(t+\\Delta t)=D(t)+ \\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +2c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    \\pm0, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -2c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Eta bestalde, prezioen batazbestekoa:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$G(t)=\\frac{p_1(t)+p_2(t)}{2},\\, \\Delta G=G(t)-G(t\\prime)\\quad\\longrightarrow\\quad \\Delta G(t+\\Delta t)=\\Delta G(t)+ \\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    \\pm0, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "KONTUZ! Paperrean esaten da $\\Delta G$ dela grafikoan agertzen dena. Niri, behintzat, $G(t)-G(0)$ ploteatuta agertzen zait eite bereko 2 dimentsiotako Random Walk-a.\n",
    "\n",
    "Bi aldagai hauek 2 dimentsiotako Random Walk bat deskribatzen dute, $D(t)=L$ eta $D(t)=-L$-n pareta xurgakorrak dituena.\n",
    "\n",
    "Ibiltari aleatorioa pareta xurgakor hauetariko batetara iristean, transakzio bat gertatzen da eta Ibiltaria hasierako (0,0) puntutik hasiko da (prozesu estokastikoari jarraiki, berriz ere transakzio bat gertatu arte). 2 dimentsiotako plano honetan, $I(n)$ transakzio denbora-tartea biziraupen-denborak erakusten du; hau da, Ibiltaria jatorritik pareta xurgatzaileetariko batera heltzen den uneraino igarotako denbora. Era berean, merkatu-prezioaren aldakuntza $\\Delta P(n)$, Ibiltariaren G ardatzeko posizioak ematen du. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed()\n",
    "L = 0.02  # L parametroa aldatzeko aukera 2Dko simulaziorako (muga xurgatzailea)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "mpl.rc('xtick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "mpl.rc('ytick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "plt.rc('text', usetex=True)\n",
    "plt.rc('font', family='serif')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7.5,7.5),dpi=200) # mxn pulgada eta dpi=dots-per-inch\n",
    "col=['g','m']\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(2):                                # Bi errealizaziotarako kalkulatu\n",
    "    G = []\n",
    "    D = []\n",
    "    p1 = 100.25\n",
    "    p2 = 100.25\n",
    "    D.append(p1-p2)\n",
    "    G.append(np.average((p1,p2)))\n",
    "\n",
    "    while np.absolute(p1-p2)<L:\n",
    "            p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)\n",
    "            p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)\n",
    "            G.append(np.average((p1,p2)))\n",
    "            D.append(p1-p2)\n",
    "    G = np.array(G)\n",
    "    G = G - G[0]\n",
    "    D = np.array(D)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.plot(G,D,lw=0.5, zorder=1,alpha=0.8)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(G[-1],D[-1], lw=3,zorder=2)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(G[0],D[0], lw=3,zorder=3)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(r\"$x=G(t)-G(0)$\", fontsize=20)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(r\"$y=D$\", fontsize=20) \n",
    "ax.set_ylim(-0.021,0.021)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(-0.025,0.025)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "fig.savefig('AEredua_2D.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Goiko grafikoan:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Puntu berdea: Hasiera puntua.\n",
    "- Beste bi puntuak: Amaiera puntuak.\n",
    "\n",
    "Ohartu amaiera puntua beti dagoela D-ren $\\pm L$ balioan. Noski, $D(t)=p_1(t)-p_2(t)$ batazbesteko prezioen arteko aldea $L$-ren berdina (justu eredu honetako $L$ parametroaren balioa $L=\\pm 0.02$ izanik) edo handiagoa denean, transakzio bat gertatzen da, eta momentu hortan, bi negoziatzaileen prezioak berdindu egiten dira, bien arteko batazbesteko preziora (transakzio-preziora, merkatu-preziora). \n",
    "\n",
    "Bestalde, eta kontuan izanik $G(t)$ aldagaiak zer errepresentatzen duen, argi dago puntu berdearen eta beste bien arteko $x$ ardatzeko distantziak $\\Delta P$-ren balioa emango digula. Hau da, ibilbide aleatorioa hasten denean, aldiune hortako merkatu-preziotik hasten gara, eta estokastikoki eboluzionatzen duten $p_1(t)$ eta $p_2(t)$ funtzioek transakzio-baldintza betetzen duten aldiunean, merkatu-prezio hori aldatu egin da. Aldaketa hori, esan bezala, puntu berdearen eta bete bien arteko distantzia horizontalari behatuta kalkula genezake. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.1.7. A Eredua - Simulazio Animatua"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Atal honetan, $(G,D)$ espazioan, _partikula_ -ren higiduraren animazioa idatzi dut. _Partikula_ -ri buruz dihardugunean, hau $(G,D)=\\left((p_1+p_2)/2,p_1-p_2\\right)$ baliodun objektua da, 2 dimentsiotan ibilbide guztiz aleatorio bat marraztuko duena, eta transakzio-baldintza ($|p_1-p_2|\\geq L$) betetzean bukatuko dena. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 1.1.7.1. Libreriak eta parametroak eta aldagaiak"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib nbagg\n",
    "\n",
    "# ----------- LIBRERIAK ------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np               \n",
    "from matplotlib import rc                  # Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.animation as animazio   # animation moduluak animazioa burutzea erraztuko digu\n",
    "from random import choice\n",
    "from random import seed\n",
    "plt.style.use('fivethirtyeight')\n",
    "\n",
    "# ----------- PARAMETROAK -----------------\n",
    "Delta_p = 0.01\n",
    "c = 0.01\n",
    "L = 0.01\n",
    "N = 5000                         # transakzio kopuru totala (guk nahibeste)\n",
    "f_i = [-Delta_p,Delta_p]         # i. negoziatzaileari dagokion ausazko zarata \n",
    "#denbora = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "# ------------ ALDAGAIAK -------------------\n",
    "D = np.zeros([N])\n",
    "G = np.zeros([N])\n",
    "p1 = 100.25           # Hasieratze balio bat (edozein jarri diet) \n",
    "p2 = 100.25"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 1.1.7.2. init() eta animatu() funtzioak"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def init():\n",
    "    \n",
    "    global D, G, p1, p2, denbora #aldagai globalak izendatzen ditut, prog. nagusian definitutakoak hemen erabili ahal izateko\n",
    "    \n",
    "    p1 = 100.25           # Hasieratze balio bat (edozein) \n",
    "    p2 = 100.25\n",
    "    \n",
    "    D[0] = p1-p2\n",
    "    D[1:]= 0.0\n",
    "    G[0] = np.average((p1,p2))\n",
    "    G[1:] = 0.0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    traiektoria1.set_data([],[])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return traiektoria1,\n",
    "\n",
    "def animatu(i):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    global D, G, p1, p2, denbora \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)\n",
    "    p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)\n",
    "    D_G = np.average((p1,p2))-G[0]    \n",
    "    D[i+1] = p1-p2\n",
    "    G[i+1] = D_G\n",
    "    \n",
    "    traiektoria1.set_data(G[1:i+1],D[1:i+1])  # 2D-ko lerroa zehaztu\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return traiektoria1,"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Animazioa aldiune jakin batean gelditzea behar dugu: prezio-diferentzia, L irabazi-marjina baino handiagoa denean. Kasu horretan, D ardatzean _partikula_ $\\pm L$-ra heltzean, simulazioa bukatu egin behar da. Hori lortzeko, _gen_function_ hau erabiliko dugu:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gen_function():\n",
    "    global D\n",
    "    i = 0\n",
    "    while (D[i]<L):\n",
    "        print(i)\n",
    "        yield i\n",
    "        i +=1 "
   ]
  },

       "    if (typeof(WebSocket) !== 'undefined') {\n",
       "        return WebSocket;\n",
       "    } else if (typeof(MozWebSocket) !== 'undefined') {\n",
       "        return MozWebSocket;\n",
       "    } else {\n",

       "              'Firefox 4 and 5 are also supported but you ' +\n",

       "mpl.figure = function(figure_id, websocket, ondownload, parent_element) {\n",
       "    this.id = figure_id;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.ws = websocket;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.supports_binary = (this.ws.binaryType != undefined);\n",
       "\n",
       "    if (!this.supports_binary) {\n",
       "        var warnings = document.getElementById(\"mpl-warnings\");\n",
       "        if (warnings) {\n",
       "            warnings.style.display = 'block';\n",
       "            warnings.textContent = (\n",
       "                \"This browser does not support binary websocket messages. \" +\n",
       "                    \"Performance may be slow.\");\n",
       "        }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.imageObj = new Image();\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.context = undefined;\n",
       "    this.message = undefined;\n",
       "    this.canvas = undefined;\n",
       "    this.rubberband_canvas = undefined;\n",

       "    this.format_dropdown = undefined;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.image_mode = 'full';\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.root = $('<div/>');\n",
       "    this._root_extra_style(this.root)\n",
       "    this.root.attr('style', 'display: inline-block');\n",
       "\n",
       "    $(parent_element).append(this.root);\n",
       "\n",
       "    this._init_header(this);\n",
       "    this._init_canvas(this);\n",
       "    this._init_toolbar(this);\n",
       "\n",
       "    var fig = this;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.waiting = false;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.ws.onopen =  function () {\n",
       "            fig.send_message(\"supports_binary\", {value: fig.supports_binary});\n",
       "            fig.send_message(\"send_image_mode\", {});\n",
       "            if (mpl.ratio != 1) {\n",
       "                fig.send_message(\"set_dpi_ratio\", {'dpi_ratio': mpl.ratio});\n",
       "            }\n",
       "            fig.send_message(\"refresh\", {});\n",
       "        }\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.imageObj.onload = function() {\n",
       "            if (fig.image_mode == 'full') {\n",
       "                // Full images could contain transparency (where diff images\n",
       "                // almost always do), so we need to clear the canvas so that\n",
       "                // there is no ghosting.\n",
       "                fig.context.clearRect(0, 0, fig.canvas.width, fig.canvas.height);\n",
       "            }\n",
       "            fig.context.drawImage(fig.imageObj, 0, 0);\n",
       "        };\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.imageObj.onunload = function() {\n",
       "        fig.ws.close();\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.ws.onmessage = this._make_on_message_function(this);\n",
       "\n",

       "mpl.figure.prototype._init_canvas = function() {\n",
       "    var fig = this;\n",
       "\n",
       "    var canvas_div = $('<div/>');\n",
       "\n",
       "    canvas_div.attr('style', 'position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0');\n",
       "\n",
       "    function canvas_keyboard_event(event) {\n",
       "        return fig.key_event(event, event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    canvas_div.keydown('key_press', canvas_keyboard_event);\n",
       "    canvas_div.keyup('key_release', canvas_keyboard_event);\n",
       "    this.canvas_div = canvas_div\n",
       "    this._canvas_extra_style(canvas_div)\n",
       "    this.root.append(canvas_div);\n",
       "\n",
       "    var canvas = $('<canvas/>');\n",
       "    canvas.addClass('mpl-canvas');\n",
       "    canvas.attr('style', \"left: 0; top: 0; z-index: 0; outline: 0\")\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.canvas = canvas[0];\n",
       "    this.context = canvas[0].getContext(\"2d\");\n",
       "\n",
       "    var backingStore = this.context.backingStorePixelRatio ||\n",
       "\tthis.context.webkitBackingStorePixelRatio ||\n",
       "\tthis.context.mozBackingStorePixelRatio ||\n",
       "\tthis.context.msBackingStorePixelRatio ||\n",
       "\tthis.context.oBackingStorePixelRatio ||\n",
       "\tthis.context.backingStorePixelRatio || 1;\n",
       "\n",
       "    mpl.ratio = (window.devicePixelRatio || 1) / backingStore;\n",
       "\n",
       "    var rubberband = $('<canvas/>');\n",
       "    rubberband.attr('style', \"position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; z-index: 1;\")\n",
       "\n",
       "    var pass_mouse_events = true;\n",
       "\n",
       "    canvas_div.resizable({\n",
       "        start: function(event, ui) {\n",
       "            pass_mouse_events = false;\n",
       "        },\n",
       "        resize: function(event, ui) {\n",
       "            fig.request_resize(ui.size.width, ui.size.height);\n",
       "        },\n",
       "        stop: function(event, ui) {\n",
       "            pass_mouse_events = true;\n",
       "            fig.request_resize(ui.size.width, ui.size.height);\n",
       "        },\n",
       "    });\n",
       "\n",
       "    function mouse_event_fn(event) {\n",
       "        if (pass_mouse_events)\n",
       "            return fig.mouse_event(event, event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    rubberband.mousedown('button_press', mouse_event_fn);\n",
       "    rubberband.mouseup('button_release', mouse_event_fn);\n",
       "    // Throttle sequential mouse events to 1 every 20ms.\n",
       "    rubberband.mousemove('motion_notify', mouse_event_fn);\n",
       "\n",
       "    rubberband.mouseenter('figure_enter', mouse_event_fn);\n",
       "    rubberband.mouseleave('figure_leave', mouse_event_fn);\n",
       "\n",
       "    canvas_div.on(\"wheel\", function (event) {\n",
       "        event = event.originalEvent;\n",
       "        event['data'] = 'scroll'\n",
       "        if (event.deltaY < 0) {\n",
       "            event.step = 1;\n",
       "        } else {\n",
       "            event.step = -1;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "        mouse_event_fn(event);\n",
       "    });\n",
       "\n",
       "    canvas_div.append(canvas);\n",
       "    canvas_div.append(rubberband);\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.rubberband = rubberband;\n",
       "    this.rubberband_canvas = rubberband[0];\n",
       "    this.rubberband_context = rubberband[0].getContext(\"2d\");\n",
       "    this.rubberband_context.strokeStyle = \"#000000\";\n",
       "\n",
       "    this._resize_canvas = function(width, height) {\n",
       "        // Keep the size of the canvas, canvas container, and rubber band\n",
       "        // canvas in synch.\n",
       "        canvas_div.css('width', width)\n",
       "        canvas_div.css('height', height)\n",
       "\n",
       "        canvas.attr('width', width * mpl.ratio);\n",
       "        canvas.attr('height', height * mpl.ratio);\n",
       "        canvas.attr('style', 'width: ' + width + 'px; height: ' + height + 'px;');\n",
       "\n",
       "        rubberband.attr('width', width);\n",
       "        rubberband.attr('height', height);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Set the figure to an initial 600x600px, this will subsequently be updated\n",
       "    // upon first draw.\n",
       "    this._resize_canvas(600, 600);\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Disable right mouse context menu.\n",
       "    $(this.rubberband_canvas).bind(\"contextmenu\",function(e){\n",
       "        return false;\n",
       "    });\n",
       "\n",
       "    function set_focus () {\n",
       "        canvas.focus();\n",
       "        canvas_div.focus();\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    window.setTimeout(set_focus, 100);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._init_toolbar = function() {\n",
       "    var fig = this;\n",
       "\n",
       "    var nav_element = $('<div/>');\n",
       "    nav_element.attr('style', 'width: 100%');\n",
       "    this.root.append(nav_element);\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Define a callback function for later on.\n",
       "    function toolbar_event(event) {\n",
       "        return fig.toolbar_button_onclick(event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    function toolbar_mouse_event(event) {\n",
       "        return fig.toolbar_button_onmouseover(event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    for(var toolbar_ind in mpl.toolbar_items) {\n",
       "        var name = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][0];\n",
       "        var tooltip = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][1];\n",
       "        var image = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][2];\n",
       "        var method_name = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][3];\n",
       "\n",
       "        if (!name) {\n",
       "            // put a spacer in here.\n",
       "            continue;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "        var button = $('<button/>');\n",
       "        button.addClass('ui-button ui-widget ui-state-default ui-corner-all ' +\n",
       "                        'ui-button-icon-only');\n",
       "        button.attr('role', 'button');\n",
       "        button.attr('aria-disabled', 'false');\n",
       "        button.click(method_name, toolbar_event);\n",
       "        button.mouseover(tooltip, toolbar_mouse_event);\n",
       "\n",
       "        var icon_img = $('<span/>');\n",
       "        icon_img.addClass('ui-button-icon-primary ui-icon');\n",
       "        icon_img.addClass(image);\n",
       "        icon_img.addClass('ui-corner-all');\n",
       "\n",
       "        var tooltip_span = $('<span/>');\n",
       "        tooltip_span.addClass('ui-button-text');\n",
       "        tooltip_span.html(tooltip);\n",
       "\n",
       "        button.append(icon_img);\n",
       "        button.append(tooltip_span);\n",
       "\n",
       "        nav_element.append(button);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    var fmt_picker_span = $('<span/>');\n",
       "\n",
       "    var fmt_picker = $('<select/>');\n",
       "    fmt_picker.addClass('mpl-toolbar-option ui-widget ui-widget-content');\n",
       "    fmt_picker_span.append(fmt_picker);\n",
       "    nav_element.append(fmt_picker_span);\n",
       "    this.format_dropdown = fmt_picker[0];\n",
       "\n",
       "    for (var ind in mpl.extensions) {\n",
       "        var fmt = mpl.extensions[ind];\n",
       "        var option = $(\n",
       "            '<option/>', {selected: fmt === mpl.default_extension}).html(fmt);\n",
       "        fmt_picker.append(option);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Add hover states to the ui-buttons\n",
       "    $( \".ui-button\" ).hover(\n",
       "        function() { $(this).addClass(\"ui-state-hover\");},\n",
       "        function() { $(this).removeClass(\"ui-state-hover\");}\n",
       "    );\n",
       "\n",
       "    var status_bar = $('<span class=\"mpl-message\"/>');\n",
       "    nav_element.append(status_bar);\n",
       "    this.message = status_bar[0];\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.request_resize = function(x_pixels, y_pixels) {\n",
       "    // Request matplotlib to resize the figure. Matplotlib will then trigger a resize in the client,\n",
       "    // which will in turn request a refresh of the image.\n",
       "    this.send_message('resize', {'width': x_pixels, 'height': y_pixels});\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.send_message = function(type, properties) {\n",
       "    properties['type'] = type;\n",
       "    properties['figure_id'] = this.id;\n",
       "    this.ws.send(JSON.stringify(properties));\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.send_draw_message = function() {\n",
       "    if (!this.waiting) {\n",
       "        this.waiting = true;\n",
       "        this.ws.send(JSON.stringify({type: \"draw\", figure_id: this.id}));\n",
       "    }\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_save = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    var format_dropdown = fig.format_dropdown;\n",
       "    var format = format_dropdown.options[format_dropdown.selectedIndex].value;\n",
       "    fig.ondownload(fig, format);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_resize = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    var size = msg['size'];\n",
       "    if (size[0] != fig.canvas.width || size[1] != fig.canvas.height) {\n",
       "        fig._resize_canvas(size[0], size[1]);\n",
       "        fig.send_message(\"refresh\", {});\n",
       "    };\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_rubberband = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    var x0 = msg['x0'] / mpl.ratio;\n",
       "    var y0 = (fig.canvas.height - msg['y0']) / mpl.ratio;\n",
       "    var x1 = msg['x1'] / mpl.ratio;\n",
       "    var y1 = (fig.canvas.height - msg['y1']) / mpl.ratio;\n",
       "    x0 = Math.floor(x0) + 0.5;\n",
       "    y0 = Math.floor(y0) + 0.5;\n",
       "    x1 = Math.floor(x1) + 0.5;\n",
       "    y1 = Math.floor(y1) + 0.5;\n",
       "    var min_x = Math.min(x0, x1);\n",
       "    var min_y = Math.min(y0, y1);\n",
       "    var width = Math.abs(x1 - x0);\n",
       "    var height = Math.abs(y1 - y0);\n",
       "\n",
       "    fig.rubberband_context.clearRect(\n",
       "        0, 0, fig.canvas.width / mpl.ratio, fig.canvas.height / mpl.ratio);\n",
       "\n",
       "    fig.rubberband_context.strokeRect(min_x, min_y, width, height);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_figure_label = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    // Updates the figure title.\n",
       "    fig.header.textContent = msg['label'];\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_cursor = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    var cursor = msg['cursor'];\n",
       "    switch(cursor)\n",
       "    {\n",
       "    case 0:\n",
       "        cursor = 'pointer';\n",
       "        break;\n",
       "    case 1:\n",
       "        cursor = 'default';\n",
       "        break;\n",
       "    case 2:\n",
       "        cursor = 'crosshair';\n",
       "        break;\n",
       "    case 3:\n",
       "        cursor = 'move';\n",
       "        break;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    fig.rubberband_canvas.style.cursor = cursor;\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_message = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    fig.message.textContent = msg['message'];\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_draw = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    // Request the server to send over a new figure.\n",
       "    fig.send_draw_message();\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_image_mode = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    fig.image_mode = msg['mode'];\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.updated_canvas_event = function() {\n",
       "    // Called whenever the canvas gets updated.\n",
       "    this.send_message(\"ack\", {});\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "// A function to construct a web socket function for onmessage handling.\n",
       "// Called in the figure constructor.\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._make_on_message_function = function(fig) {\n",
       "    return function socket_on_message(evt) {\n",
       "        if (evt.data instanceof Blob) {\n",
       "            /* FIXME: We get \"Resource interpreted as Image but\n",
       "             * transferred with MIME type text/plain:\" errors on\n",
       "             * Chrome.  But how to set the MIME type?  It doesn't seem\n",
       "             * to be part of the websocket stream */\n",
       "            evt.data.type = \"image/png\";\n",
       "\n",
       "            /* Free the memory for the previous frames */\n",
       "            if (fig.imageObj.src) {\n",
       "                (window.URL || window.webkitURL).revokeObjectURL(\n",
       "                    fig.imageObj.src);\n",
       "            }\n",
       "\n",
       "            fig.imageObj.src = (window.URL || window.webkitURL).createObjectURL(\n",
       "                evt.data);\n",
       "            fig.updated_canvas_event();\n",
       "            fig.waiting = false;\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "        else if (typeof evt.data === 'string' && evt.data.slice(0, 21) == \"data:image/png;base64\") {\n",
       "            fig.imageObj.src = evt.data;\n",
       "            fig.updated_canvas_event();\n",
       "            fig.waiting = false;\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "\n",
       "        var msg = JSON.parse(evt.data);\n",
       "        var msg_type = msg['type'];\n",
       "\n",
       "        // Call the  \"handle_{type}\" callback, which takes\n",
       "        // the figure and JSON message as its only arguments.\n",
       "        try {\n",
       "            var callback = fig[\"handle_\" + msg_type];\n",
       "        } catch (e) {\n",
       "            console.log(\"No handler for the '\" + msg_type + \"' message type: \", msg);\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "        }\n",
       "\n",
       "        if (callback) {\n",
       "            try {\n",
       "                // console.log(\"Handling '\" + msg_type + \"' message: \", msg);\n",
       "                callback(fig, msg);\n",
       "            } catch (e) {\n",
       "                console.log(\"Exception inside the 'handler_\" + msg_type + \"' callback:\", e, e.stack, msg);\n",
       "            }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "    };\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "// from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1114465/getting-mouse-location-in-canvas\n",
       "mpl.findpos = function(e) {\n",
       "    //this section is from http://www.quirksmode.org/js/events_properties.html\n",
       "    var targ;\n",
       "    if (!e)\n",
       "        e = window.event;\n",
       "    if (e.target)\n",
       "        targ = e.target;\n",
       "    else if (e.srcElement)\n",
       "        targ = e.srcElement;\n",
       "    if (targ.nodeType == 3) // defeat Safari bug\n",
       "        targ = targ.parentNode;\n",
       "\n",
       "    // jQuery normalizes the pageX and pageY\n",
       "    // pageX,Y are the mouse positions relative to the document\n",
       "    // offset() returns the position of the element relative to the document\n",
       "    var x = e.pageX - $(targ).offset().left;\n",
       "    var y = e.pageY - $(targ).offset().top;\n",
       "\n",
       "    return {\"x\": x, \"y\": y};\n",
       "};\n",
       "\n",
       "/*\n",
       " * return a copy of an object with only non-object keys\n",
       " * we need this to avoid circular references\n",
       " * http://stackoverflow.com/a/24161582/3208463\n",
       " */\n",
       "function simpleKeys (original) {\n",
       "  return Object.keys(original).reduce(function (obj, key) {\n",
       "    if (typeof original[key] !== 'object')\n",
       "        obj[key] = original[key]\n",
       "    return obj;\n",
       "  }, {});\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.mouse_event = function(event, name) {\n",
       "    var canvas_pos = mpl.findpos(event)\n",
       "\n",
       "    if (name === 'button_press')\n",
       "    {\n",
       "        this.canvas.focus();\n",
       "        this.canvas_div.focus();\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    var x = canvas_pos.x * mpl.ratio;\n",
       "    var y = canvas_pos.y * mpl.ratio;\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.send_message(name, {x: x, y: y, button: event.button,\n",
       "                             step: event.step,\n",
       "                             guiEvent: simpleKeys(event)});\n",
       "\n",
       "    /* This prevents the web browser from automatically changing to\n",
       "     * the text insertion cursor when the button is pressed.  We want\n",
       "     * to control all of the cursor setting manually through the\n",
       "     * 'cursor' event from matplotlib */\n",
       "    event.preventDefault();\n",
       "    return false;\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._key_event_extra = function(event, name) {\n",
       "    // Handle any extra behaviour associated with a key event\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.key_event = function(event, name) {\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Prevent repeat events\n",
       "    if (name == 'key_press')\n",
       "    {\n",
       "        if (event.which === this._key)\n",
       "            return;\n",
       "        else\n",
       "            this._key = event.which;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    if (name == 'key_release')\n",
       "        this._key = null;\n",
       "\n",
       "    var value = '';\n",
       "    if (event.ctrlKey && event.which != 17)\n",
       "        value += \"ctrl+\";\n",
       "    if (event.altKey && event.which != 18)\n",
       "        value += \"alt+\";\n",
       "    if (event.shiftKey && event.which != 16)\n",
       "        value += \"shift+\";\n",
       "\n",
       "    value += 'k';\n",
       "    value += event.which.toString();\n",
       "\n",
       "    this._key_event_extra(event, name);\n",
       "\n",
       "    this.send_message(name, {key: value,\n",
       "                             guiEvent: simpleKeys(event)});\n",
       "    return false;\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.toolbar_button_onclick = function(name) {\n",
       "    if (name == 'download') {\n",
       "        this.handle_save(this, null);\n",
       "    } else {\n",
       "        this.send_message(\"toolbar_button\", {name: name});\n",
       "    }\n",
       "};\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.toolbar_button_onmouseover = function(tooltip) {\n",
       "    this.message.textContent = tooltip;\n",
       "};\n",
       "mpl.toolbar_items = [[\"Home\", \"Reset original view\", \"fa fa-home icon-home\", \"home\"], [\"Back\", \"Back to previous view\", \"fa fa-arrow-left icon-arrow-left\", \"back\"], [\"Forward\", \"Forward to next view\", \"fa fa-arrow-right icon-arrow-right\", \"forward\"], [\"\", \"\", \"\", \"\"], [\"Pan\", \"Pan axes with left mouse, zoom with right\", \"fa fa-arrows icon-move\", \"pan\"], [\"Zoom\", \"Zoom to rectangle\", \"fa fa-square-o icon-check-empty\", \"zoom\"], [\"\", \"\", \"\", \"\"], [\"Download\", \"Download plot\", \"fa fa-floppy-o icon-save\", \"download\"]];\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.extensions = [\"eps\", \"jpeg\", \"pdf\", \"png\", \"ps\", \"raw\", \"svg\", \"tif\"];\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.default_extension = \"png\";var comm_websocket_adapter = function(comm) {\n",
       "    // Create a \"websocket\"-like object which calls the given IPython comm\n",
       "    // object with the appropriate methods. Currently this is a non binary\n",
       "    // socket, so there is still some room for performance tuning.\n",
       "    var ws = {};\n",
       "\n",
       "    ws.close = function() {\n",
       "        comm.close()\n",
       "    };\n",
       "    ws.send = function(m) {\n",
       "        //console.log('sending', m);\n",
       "        comm.send(m);\n",
       "    };\n",
       "    // Register the callback with on_msg.\n",
       "    comm.on_msg(function(msg) {\n",
       "        //console.log('receiving', msg['content']['data'], msg);\n",
       "        // Pass the mpl event to the overridden (by mpl) onmessage function.\n",
       "        ws.onmessage(msg['content']['data'])\n",
       "    });\n",
       "    return ws;\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.mpl_figure_comm = function(comm, msg) {\n",
       "    // This is the function which gets called when the mpl process\n",
       "    // starts-up an IPython Comm through the \"matplotlib\" channel.\n",
       "\n",
       "    var id = msg.content.data.id;\n",
       "    // Get hold of the div created by the display call when the Comm\n",
       "    // socket was opened in Python.\n",
       "    var element = $(\"#\" + id);\n",
       "    var ws_proxy = comm_websocket_adapter(comm)\n",
       "\n",
       "    function ondownload(figure, format) {\n",
       "        window.open(figure.imageObj.src);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    var fig = new mpl.figure(id, ws_proxy,\n",
       "                           ondownload,\n",
       "                           element.get(0));\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Call onopen now - mpl needs it, as it is assuming we've passed it a real\n",
       "    // web socket which is closed, not our websocket->open comm proxy.\n",
       "    ws_proxy.onopen();\n",
       "\n",
       "    fig.parent_element = element.get(0);\n",
       "    fig.cell_info = mpl.find_output_cell(\"<div id='\" + id + \"'></div>\");\n",
       "    if (!fig.cell_info) {\n",
       "        console.error(\"Failed to find cell for figure\", id, fig);\n",
       "        return;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    var output_index = fig.cell_info[2]\n",
       "    var cell = fig.cell_info[0];\n",
       "\n",
       "};\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_close = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    var width = fig.canvas.width/mpl.ratio\n",
       "    fig.root.unbind('remove')\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Update the output cell to use the data from the current canvas.\n",
       "    fig.push_to_output();\n",
       "    var dataURL = fig.canvas.toDataURL();\n",
       "    // Re-enable the keyboard manager in IPython - without this line, in FF,\n",
       "    // the notebook keyboard shortcuts fail.\n",
       "    IPython.keyboard_manager.enable()\n",
       "    $(fig.parent_element).html('<img src=\"' + dataURL + '\" width=\"' + width + '\">');\n",
       "    fig.close_ws(fig, msg);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.close_ws = function(fig, msg){\n",
       "    fig.send_message('closing', msg);\n",
       "    // fig.ws.close()\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.push_to_output = function(remove_interactive) {\n",
       "    // Turn the data on the canvas into data in the output cell.\n",
       "    var width = this.canvas.width/mpl.ratio\n",
       "    var dataURL = this.canvas.toDataURL();\n",
       "    this.cell_info[1]['text/html'] = '<img src=\"' + dataURL + '\" width=\"' + width + '\">';\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.updated_canvas_event = function() {\n",
       "    // Tell IPython that the notebook contents must change.\n",
       "    IPython.notebook.set_dirty(true);\n",
       "    this.send_message(\"ack\", {});\n",
       "    var fig = this;\n",
       "    // Wait a second, then push the new image to the DOM so\n",
       "    // that it is saved nicely (might be nice to debounce this).\n",
       "    setTimeout(function () { fig.push_to_output() }, 1000);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._init_toolbar = function() {\n",
       "    var fig = this;\n",
       "\n",
       "    var nav_element = $('<div/>');\n",
       "    nav_element.attr('style', 'width: 100%');\n",
       "    this.root.append(nav_element);\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Define a callback function for later on.\n",
       "    function toolbar_event(event) {\n",
       "        return fig.toolbar_button_onclick(event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    function toolbar_mouse_event(event) {\n",
       "        return fig.toolbar_button_onmouseover(event['data']);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    for(var toolbar_ind in mpl.toolbar_items){\n",
       "        var name = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][0];\n",
       "        var tooltip = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][1];\n",
       "        var image = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][2];\n",
       "        var method_name = mpl.toolbar_items[toolbar_ind][3];\n",
       "\n",
       "        if (!name) { continue; };\n",
       "\n",
       "        var button = $('<button class=\"btn btn-default\" href=\"#\" title=\"' + name + '\"><i class=\"fa ' + image + ' fa-lg\"></i></button>');\n",
       "        button.click(method_name, toolbar_event);\n",
       "        button.mouseover(tooltip, toolbar_mouse_event);\n",
       "        nav_element.append(button);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Add the status bar.\n",
       "    var status_bar = $('<span class=\"mpl-message\" style=\"text-align:right; float: right;\"/>');\n",
       "    nav_element.append(status_bar);\n",
       "    this.message = status_bar[0];\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Add the close button to the window.\n",
       "    var buttongrp = $('<div class=\"btn-group inline pull-right\"></div>');\n",
       "    var button = $('<button class=\"btn btn-mini btn-primary\" href=\"#\" title=\"Stop Interaction\"><i class=\"fa fa-power-off icon-remove icon-large\"></i></button>');\n",
       "    button.click(function (evt) { fig.handle_close(fig, {}); } );\n",
       "    button.mouseover('Stop Interaction', toolbar_mouse_event);\n",
       "    buttongrp.append(button);\n",
       "    var titlebar = this.root.find($('.ui-dialog-titlebar'));\n",
       "    titlebar.prepend(buttongrp);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._root_extra_style = function(el){\n",
       "    var fig = this\n",
       "    el.on(\"remove\", function(){\n",
       "\tfig.close_ws(fig, {});\n",
       "    });\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._canvas_extra_style = function(el){\n",
       "    // this is important to make the div 'focusable\n",
       "    el.attr('tabindex', 0)\n",
       "    // reach out to IPython and tell the keyboard manager to turn it's self\n",
       "    // off when our div gets focus\n",
       "\n",
       "    // location in version 3\n",
       "    if (IPython.notebook.keyboard_manager) {\n",
       "        IPython.notebook.keyboard_manager.register_events(el);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    else {\n",
       "        // location in version 2\n",
       "        IPython.keyboard_manager.register_events(el);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype._key_event_extra = function(event, name) {\n",
       "    var manager = IPython.notebook.keyboard_manager;\n",
       "    if (!manager)\n",
       "        manager = IPython.keyboard_manager;\n",
       "\n",
       "    // Check for shift+enter\n",
       "    if (event.shiftKey && event.which == 13) {\n",
       "        this.canvas_div.blur();\n",
       "        event.shiftKey = false;\n",
       "        // Send a \"J\" for go to next cell\n",
       "        event.which = 74;\n",
       "        event.keyCode = 74;\n",
       "        manager.command_mode();\n",
       "        manager.handle_keydown(event);\n",
       "    }\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.figure.prototype.handle_save = function(fig, msg) {\n",
       "    fig.ondownload(fig, null);\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "\n",
       "mpl.find_output_cell = function(html_output) {\n",
       "    // Return the cell and output element which can be found *uniquely* in the notebook.\n",
       "    // Note - this is a bit hacky, but it is done because the \"notebook_saving.Notebook\"\n",
       "    // IPython event is triggered only after the cells have been serialised, which for\n",
       "    // our purposes (turning an active figure into a static one), is too late.\n",
       "    var cells = IPython.notebook.get_cells();\n",
       "    var ncells = cells.length;\n",
       "    for (var i=0; i<ncells; i++) {\n",
       "        var cell = cells[i];\n",
       "        if (cell.cell_type === 'code'){\n",
       "            for (var j=0; j<cell.output_area.outputs.length; j++) {\n",
       "                var data = cell.output_area.outputs[j];\n",
       "                if (data.data) {\n",
       "                    // IPython >= 3 moved mimebundle to data attribute of output\n",
       "                    data = data.data;\n",
       "                }\n",
       "                if (data['text/html'] == html_output) {\n",
       "                    return [cell, data, j];\n",
       "                }\n",
       "            }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "}\n",
       "\n",
       "// Register the function which deals with the matplotlib target/channel.\n",
       "// The kernel may be null if the page has been refreshed.\n",
       "if (IPython.notebook.kernel != null) {\n",
       "    IPython.notebook.kernel.comm_manager.register_target('matplotlib', mpl.mpl_figure_comm);\n",
       "}\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },

       "<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"

     "output_type": "display_data"

    "## 1.2. B Eredua - Simulazio Estatikoa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Atal honetan, prezioen aldaketetan zentratuko gara. \n",
    "\n",
    "A Ereduko itzulkinen probabilitate banaketa, banaketa esponentzial batez ezaugarritu daiteke, baina merkatu erreal batean hau ez da, oro har, behatzen dena. Merkatu errealak deskribatzerakoan, hauek berretura-lege jakin batzuk jarraitzen dituztela behatu da enpirikoki. Era hontako berredura-legeak konputazionalki gara daitezke _trend-following_ (moda-jarraitze) predikzioaren efektuaz baliaturik. \n",
    "\n",
    "Efektu hau gure merkatari-eredu estokastikora egokitzeko, $d\\langle \\Delta P \\rangle_M \\Delta t$ gaia gehituko diogu aurreko ereduko prezioaren higidura-ekuazioari:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$p_i(t+\\Delta t)=p_i(t)+d\\langle \\Delta P \\rangle_M\\Delta t + cf_i(t)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$f_i(t)=\\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -\\Delta p, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}\\quad i=1,2$$\n",
    "\n",
    "non\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\langle \\Delta P \\rangle_M = \\frac{2}{M(M+1)}\\sum_{k=0}^{M-1}(M-k)\\Delta P(n-k)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\Delta P(n)=P(n)-P(n-1)$ aldagaiak, n. _tick_ -ean gertatu den prezio-aldakuntza adierazten du. Bestalde, $\\langle \\Delta P \\rangle_M$ M tick-etan zeharreko batazbesteko balio mugikorra da, era linealean txikitzen dihoazen pisuekin. $d$ parametroak Merkatu Eredu hau karakterizatzen du: hauxe da, hain zuzen ere, merkatarien estrategiari buruzko informazioa gordetzen duena. $d>0$ duen merkatari bati _trend follower_ (moda jarraitzaile) deritzogu, eta honek, etortzeke dauden merkatu-prezioak aurresaten ditu iraganeko prezio-maldetan oinarrituta: hauek gorakorrak baziren, prezioak gorantz bultzatuko ditu, eta alderantziz prezioak jaisten bazihoazten. $d<0$-ko merkatariei, ordea, _contrarian_ deritzegu (aurkariak), eta hauen aburuz, etorkizuneko merkatu-prezioen joera iraganeko \"modaren\" kontra joango dira. Hau da, momentuko, oraineko merkatu-prezioak maximo/minimo lokal batetatik hurbil daudela uste dute. \n",
    "\n",
    "Efektu hau A Ereduari gehituz:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$D(t+\\Delta t)=D(t)+ \\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +2c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    \\pm0, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -2c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\Delta G(t+\\Delta t)=\\Delta G(t)+ d\\langle \\Delta P\\rangle_M + \\begin{cases}\n",
    "    +c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    \\pm0, & \\text{(1/2 prob.)}\\\\\n",
    "    -c\\Delta p,& \\text{(1/4 prob.)}\n",
    "\\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**2D-ko random Walk-a**\n",
    "\n",
    "Hastapen- eta mugalde-baldintzak ez dira aldatzen. Baina ohartu, fluxu horizontal bat agertzen dela kasu honetan, $d\\langle \\Delta P\\rangle_M$-ren proportzionala dena. Hau da, $D(t)$ A Ereduko aldagaiaren adierazpenarekin bat dator, baina ez da hau gertatzen $\\Delta G(t)$-rekin: xurgapen-puntuaren eta jatorriaren x-ardatzeko distantzia, bigarren kasu honetan, handiagoa izango da A Ereduan baino. Ostera, mugimendu bertikalak A Eredukoaren baliokideak direnez, transakzio denbora-tarteak berdinak izango dira. Fluxuaren indarra, $d$ parametroaren eta azken prezio-aldakuntzen araberakoa izango da. \n",
    "\n",
    "Merkatu-prezioaren aldakuntza:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\Delta P (n+1)=I(n)d\\langle \\Delta P\\rangle_M + F(n)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ekuazioaren eskumaldeko lehenengo gaiak, fluxuaren eraginez gertatzen den prezio-aldaketa adierazten du. Bigarren gaia A Eredukoaren identikoa da.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.2.1. Libreriak, parametroak eta aldagaien hasieratzea"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "#----------- LIBRERIAK ----------------\n",
    "       \n",
    "# Libreria orokorrak\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import rc                  # Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.mlab as mlab\n",
    "import datetime\n",
    "import math\n",
    "from random import choice\n",
    "from random import seed\n",
    "# Merkatu errealetako datuak irakurtzeko baliabideak\n",
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('fivethirtyeight')\n",
    "\n",
    "#----------- PARAMETROAK --------------\n",
    "Delta_p = 0.01\n",
    "c = 0.01\n",
    "L = 0.01\n",
    "N = 5000                         # transakzio kopuru totala (guk nahibeste)\n",
    "f_i = [-Delta_p,Delta_p]         # i. negoziatzaileari dagokion ausazko zarata \n",
    "dt = Delta_p*Delta_p\n",
    "tick = 0\n",
    "denbora = 0\n",
    "d = 1.25                         # Merkatariaren estrategia-parametroa (Txikia jarri, prezio aldaketa hain bortitza izan ez daiten)\n",
    "M = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "#------------ ALDAGAIAK --------------\n",
    "p1 = 100.25           # Hasieratze balio bat (edozein jarri diet) \n",
    "p2 = 100.25\n",
    "P_n = np.zeros([N])   # Merkatuko Prezioa\n",
    "I_n = np.zeros([N])   # (n-1) eta n. transakzioen arteko denbora-tartea\n",
    "d_Pn = np.zeros([N])\n",
    "Delta_PM = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "#---------- FUNTZIO BALIAG. ----------\n",
    "\n",
    "def normalizatu(data):                       # normalizazio hau egiten da bariantza unitarioa lortzeko (hau gabe ere egin daiteke)\n",
    "    return ((data)/np.sqrt(np.var(data)))\n",
    "\n",
    "def itzulkin_log(Pt,tau=1):                  # Denbora-serie baten itzulkin logaritmikoa bueltatuko digun funtzioa\n",
    "    return np.log(Pt[tau:])-np.log(Pt[0:-tau])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.2.2. Merkatu prezioen eta transakzio-denboren kalkulua"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Kodea exekutatzeko, beheko testu-zelda _Code_ zelda bezala exekutatu. Orain _Markdown_ zelda gisan dago, lana exekutatzean, prozesua bizkortzeko, testu-fitxategia erabili delako datuak berreskuratzeko."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(12345)\n",
    "\n",
    "startTime = datetime.datetime.now() \n",
    "\n",
    "while tick<N:                                   # Guk nahi izandako transakzio kopurura heltzen ez den bitartean  \n",
    "        \n",
    "    while np.absolute(p1-p2)<L:                                # Transakzio baldintza betetzen ez den bitartean\n",
    "        p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i) + d*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "        p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i) + d*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "        denbora += 1\n",
    "    avg = (p1+p2)/2\n",
    "    p1, p2 = avg, avg\n",
    "    P_n[tick] = avg\n",
    "    I_n[tick] = denbora\n",
    "    \n",
    "    d_Pn[tick] = P_n[tick] - P_n[np.max([0,tick-1])]            # \\Delta P(n) = P(n) - P(n-1) gorde\n",
    "    tick += 1\n",
    "    tick_0 = np.max([0, tick - M])\n",
    "    M_real = tick - tick_0                                      # M-ren balio erreala, size(P_n)<M denean\n",
    "    pisuak  = np.array(range(1,M_real+1))*2.0/(M_real*(M_real+1))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Delta_PM = pisuak.dot(d_Pn[tick_0:tick])                    #tick aldiune honetarako Delta_PM kalkulatu\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "endTime = datetime.datetime.now()\n",
    "T_osoa = endTime-startTime\n",
    "print('Exekuzioko denbora: ', T_osoa)\n",
    "\n",
    "np.savetxt('B_Eredua_dpos.txt',np.transpose([I_n, P_n])) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.2.3. Aldagaien irudikapena"
   ]

    "b_x.set_ylabel(r\"Transakzio tartea $I(n)$\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "b_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (\\textit{tick}-etan)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "c_x.plot(d_prezioa,c='r',alpha=0.6,lw=2)\n",
    "c_x.set_ylabel(r\"Prezioaren itzulkin logaritmikoa\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "c_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (\\textit{tick}-etan)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "t_kop = \"Transakzio kopurua:\"+str(N)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(t_kop)"

    "## 1.3. A eta B Eredu estokastikoen arteko alderaketa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A eta B Ereduen arteko ezberdintasun nagusia zera da: bigarrenean, merkatariek merkatuko prezioen historia kontuan izango dutela prezioak eguneratzeko. Eta bertsio hau, hobetua da, zergatik? Errealitatera gehiago hurbiltzen delako: giza-portaera kontuan hartzen du. Kontzeptualki, hori da bigarrena lehenengoaren gainetik aukeratzeko arrazoia. Praktikan, nola ikus daiteke bi hauen arteko aldea?\n",
    "\n",
    "B Ereduan, A Ereduan ez bezala, joera-jarraitze efektua sartuko da da. Efektu hau gehituz, merkatuaren parte diren merkatarien joera ezberdinak simulatu daitezke. Joera horiek, merkatu prezioetan eragin zuzena izango dute. \n",
    "\n",
    "Hau hobeto aztertzeko, bi ibilbide aleatorio (random walk) gauzatuko ditugu, bat A Eredua erabilita ta bestea B Ereduarekin. Bigarren honetan, kontsideratuko dugu merkatariak joera-jarraitzaileak direla ($d>0$). Bestalde, $M=1$ finkatuko da: merkatariek aldiuneko _tendentzia_ zein den zehazteko azken prezio-igoera baino ez dute kontuan izango. \n",
    "\n",
    "Aldaraketa doia izan daiten, zenbaki aleatorioen sekuentzia bera erabiliko dugu, _hazi_ (seed) berdina hasieratuz bientzat. Hortaz aparte, gainontzeko dena berdina izango da, d parametroa izan ezik: A Ereduaren kasuan 0-ra berdinduko dugu. "
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Prezioak denboran zehar izan duen bilakaera ikustean, joera jarraitzen duten partaideen portaera erraz identifika daiteke (laranjaz irudikatuta): prezioak gorantz edo beherantz egitean, eboluzio honek zenbait _tick_ irauten du. Denbora luzean mantentzen den joerarik ez da A Ereduarekin antzematen. Prezioen itzulkinei dagokienez, askoz ere balio puntual handiagoak ikusten dira oraingoan (B Ereduarekin agertzen diren itzulkinak, 15 aldiz desbideratze estandarrekoak dira). Azkenik, azpimarratu behar da, behin ere, transakzio-tartea berdin-berdina dela bi ereduentzat, 2D-ko ibilbide aleatorioa aztertzean aurreikusi zen bezala.\n",
    "\n",
    "**3.2 A Eredua VS B Eredua - 2Dko Simulazioa**\n",
    "\n",
    "Alderaketa bera egin daiteke 2 dimentsiotan, $(G,D)$ espazioan, A Ereduarekin egin zen bezala."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x1600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# SIMULAZIORAKO PARAMETROAK\n",
    "Delta_PM = 0.01\n",
    "colour = ['c','m']                                # Plot-a egiteko koloreak\n",
    "d = [0,1.5]                                       # d-ren balioa Model 1-erako eta Model 3-rako\n",
    "\n",
    "# Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "mpl.rc('xtick', labelsize=16) \n",
    "mpl.rc('ytick', labelsize=16) \n",
    "plt.rc('text', usetex=True)\n",
    "plt.rc('font', family='serif')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,8),dpi=200) # mxn pulgada eta dpi=dots-per-inch\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(2):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    np.random.seed(123456789)\n",
    "    G = []\n",
    "    D = []\n",
    "    p1 = 100.25\n",
    "    p2 = 100.25\n",
    "    D.append(p1-p2)\n",
    "    G.append(np.average((p1,p2)))\n",
    "\n",
    "    while np.absolute(p1-p2)<L:\n",
    "            p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)+d[i]*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "            p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i)+d[i]*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "            G.append(np.average((p1,p2)))\n",
    "            D.append(p1-p2)\n",
    "\n",
    "    G = np.array(G)\n",
    "    G = G - G[0]\n",
    "    D = np.array(D)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax.plot(G,D, lw=1, zorder=1, label=r\"d=\"+str(d[i]), alpha = 0.8)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(G[-1],D[-1], zorder=2,lw=3)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(G[0],D[0], zorder=3,lw=3)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(r\"$x=G(t)-G(0)$\", fontsize=20)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(r\"$y=D$\", fontsize=20)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(-0.01,0.01)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "fig.savefig('B_Eredua_2D.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Goiko irudian, $\\langle\\Delta P\\rangle_M = 0.01$ ezarri da, eta horrek esan nahi du simulazio horretan, bereziki, partaideek onartzen dutela prezioa igotzen ari zela iragan hurbilean. A Ereduarekin lortzen den ibilbidea laranjaz dago, eta B Ereduari dagokiona, berriz, urdinez. Ikus daitekeenez, ibilbide biak grisez markatutako puntu beretik hasten dira, eta urrats kopuru bera hartzen dute muga xurgatzailera (behekoa, kasu honetan) iristeko. Izan ere, $D$-ren dinamika berbera da bai A Ereduan, bai B Ereduan. Beraz, transakzio-tartea berbera izango da, $D$ baita transakzioaren baldintza zehazten duen aldagaia. \n",
    "\n",
    "Bi ereduen arteko aldea, $G$ ardatz horizontalean zehar egindako mugimenduan datza. Hemen, memoria-gai gehigarriak $G$ norabide positiboan fluxu bat gehitzen du, zentzu lehenetsia (positiboa, kasu honetan) eragiten duen fluxu bat, ibilbidea eskuinerantz tenkatzen duena eta $d\\langle\\Delta P\\rangle_M $-ren proportzionala dena. Simulaziotik lortzen den emaitza, irudia aztertuz gero, argi dago: B Ereduan parte hartzen dutenek transakzio bat egiten dute, eta horrek akzioen prezioa gorantz bultzatzen du; A Ereduan, berriz, prezioa jaitsi egiten da.\n",
    "\n",
    "B Ereduarekin joera-jarraitzaileak simulatzen direnez, eta iraganean merkatuko prezioa handitzen ari zela suposatuz, emaitza ez da harritzekoa. Hau da, B Ereduarekin sortu den merkatuan, partaideak, joera-jarraitzaileak dira, eta burutu den transakzio bakarreko simulazioan, hauek merkatu-prezioa gorantz bultzatu dute (iragan hurbileko portaera jarraituz)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.4. B Ereduko _d_ parametroaren izaera"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Aurreko notebook-ei nolabaiteko zentzu orokorrago bat emateko, moda-jarraitze (trend-following) honen portaerak burtsako prezioengan nolako eragina duen erakutsiko dugu. \n",
    "\n",
    "Adibidez, bisualki, zein litzateke aurkari baten eta moda-jarraitzaile baten arteko ezberdintasuna? Burtsan, honelako portaerak identifikatzeko gai izango ginateke begirada soil batez? Honetarako, aurreko simulazio-kodea pixka bat aldatuko dugu. \n",
    "\n",
    "Notebook hontan $d$ parametroaren balioa aldatuz joango gara, denboran zehar, honek merkatuan duen eragina ikusteko. Horretarako:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. $n=1$-etik $n=1000$ tick-eraino, $d=-1.0$ izango da: merkatariak aurkariak dira, eta hortaz, uste dute etorkizuneko prezioak azkenengo modaren aurka joango direla. \n",
    "\n",
    "2. Hurrengo $n=1001$-etik $n=2000$-ra, $d=0.0$ zehaztuko dugu, non merkatariak ibiltari aleatorio sinpleak diren. \n",
    "\n",
    "3. Eta merkatariak moda-jarraitzaileak izango dira, $d=1.0$, 2001 eta 3000 tick artean, eta beraz, hauen ustez, etorkizun hurbileko prezioak azken prezio-aldaketen batez besteko mugikorraren proportzionalak izango dira. \n",
    "\n",
    "4. Azkenik, 3001-etik 4000 tick-era, merkatariek beraien iraganari so egingo die: $d$, burtsako azken merkatu-prezioen batez besteko ibiltariaren araberakoa izango da. Batez besteko ibiltaria positiboa bada, hots, burtsa igotzen bazihoan, $d>0$ izango da eta merkatuan moda-jarraitzaileak izango ditugu. Bestalde, batez besteko ibiltaria negatiboa bada (edo bestela esanda, burtsa jeitsiz bazihoan), $d<0$ izango dugu eta honela, aurkariak diren merkatariak modelatuko dira. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.4.1. Libreriak, parametroak eta aldaiak"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "#----------- LIBRERIAK ----------------\n",
    "       \n",
    "# Libreria orokorrak\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import rc                  # Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.mlab as mlab\n",
    "import datetime\n",
    "from matplotlib import rc\n",
    "from random import choice\n",
    "from random import seed\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('bmh')\n",
    "\n",
    "#----------- PARAMETROAK --------------\n",
    "Delta_p = 0.01\n",
    "c = 0.01\n",
    "L = 0.01\n",
    "N = 4000                         # transakzio kopuru totala (guk nahibeste)\n",
    "f_i = [-Delta_p,Delta_p]         # i. negoziatzaileari dagokion ausazko zarata \n",
    "dt = Delta_p*Delta_p\n",
    "tick = 0\n",
    "denbora = 0\n",
    "M = 10\n",
    "\n",
    "#------------ ALDAGAIAK --------------\n",
    "p1 = 100.25           # Hasieratze balio bat (edozein jarri diet) \n",
    "p2 = 100.25\n",
    "P_n = np.zeros([N])   # Merkatuko Prezioa\n",
    "I_n = np.zeros([N])   # (n-1) eta n. transakzioen arteko denbora-tartea\n",
    "d_Pn = np.zeros([N])\n",
    "Delta_PM = 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "#---------- FUNTZIO BALIAG. ----------\n",
    "def normalizatu(data):                       # normalizazio hau egiten da bariantza unitarioa lortzeko (hau gabe ere egin daiteke)\n",
    "    return ((data)/np.sqrt(np.var(data)))\n",
    "\n",
    "def itzulkin_log(Pt,tau=1):                  # Denbora-serie baten itzulkin logaritmikoa bueltatuko digun funtzioa\n",
    "    return np.log(Pt[tau:])-np.log(Pt[0:-tau])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.4.2. Datuen Kalkuloa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Exekuzioko denbora:  0:06:03.674494\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(12345)\n",
    "\n",
    "startTime = datetime.datetime.now() \n",
    "\n",
    "while tick<N:                                                  # Guk nahi izandako transakzio kopurura heltzen ez den bitartean  \n",
    "        \n",
    "    if tick<=N/4:                                              # d parametroaren aukeraketa\n",
    "        d = -1.0\n",
    "    elif tick<=N/2:\n",
    "        d = 0\n",
    "    elif tick<=3*N/4:\n",
    "        d = 1.0\n",
    "    elif Delta_PM<0:\n",
    "        d = -1.0\n",
    "    else: \n",
    "        d = 1.0\n",
    "    while np.absolute(p1-p2)<L:                                # Transakzio baldintza betetzen ez den bitartean\n",
    "        p1 = p1 + c*np.random.choice(f_i) + d*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "        p2 = p2 + c*np.random.choice(f_i) + d*Delta_PM*dt\n",
    "        denbora += 1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    avg = (p1+p2)/2\n",
    "    p1, p2 = avg, avg\n",
    "    P_n[tick] = avg\n",
    "    I_n[tick] = denbora\n",
    "    \n",
    "    d_Pn[tick] = P_n[tick] - P_n[np.max([0,tick-1])]            # \\Delta P(n) = P(n) - P(n-1) gorde (baliteke P(n-1)\n",
    "    tick += 1\n",
    "    tick_0 = np.max([0, tick - M])\n",
    "    M_real = tick - tick_0                                      # M-ren balio erreala, size(P_n)<M denean\n",
    "    pisuak  = np.array(range(1,M_real+1))*2.0/(M_real*(M_real+1))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Delta_PM = pisuak.dot(d_Pn[tick_0:tick])                    #tick aldiune honetarako Delta_PM kalkulatu\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "endTime = datetime.datetime.now()\n",
    "T_osoa = endTime-startTime\n",
    "print('Exekuzioko denbora: ', T_osoa)\n",
    "\n",
    "np.savetxt('model3_d_aldakor.txt',np.transpose([I_n, P_n])) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.4.3. Datuen irudikapena"

    "# --------- PLOTTING-A ----------------\n",
    "I_n,P_n=np.loadtxt('model3_d_aldakor.txt',unpack=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "tick_1 = np.linspace(0,999,1000)\n",
    "tick_2 = np.linspace(1000,1999,1000)\n",
    "tick_3 = np.linspace(2000,2999,1000)\n",
    "tick_4 = np.linspace(3000,3999,1000)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Latex-en idazteko\n",
    "mpl.rc('xtick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "mpl.rc('ytick', labelsize=20) \n",
    "plt.rc('text', usetex=True)\n",
    "plt.rc('font', family='serif')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, a_x = plt.subplots(figsize=(17,6), dpi=300)\n",
    "a_x.plot(tick_1, P_n[0:1000], c='c', alpha=0.7, lw=2,label=\"$d=-1.0$\")\n",
    "a_x.plot(tick_2, P_n[1000:2000], c='r', alpha=0.7, lw=2,label=\"$d=0$\")\n",
    "a_x.plot(tick_3, P_n[2000:3000],c='g', alpha=0.7, lw=2,label=\"$d=1.0$\")\n",
    "a_x.plot(tick_4, P_n[3000:],c='m', alpha=0.7, lw=2,label=r\"$d=1\\cdot \\textrm{sign}(\\Delta P_M)$\")\n",
    "a_x.set_ylabel(r\"$P(n)$ Merkatu-prezioa\",fontsize=22)\n",
    "a_x.set_xlabel(r\"Denbora (tick)\",fontsize=20)\n",
    "for i in [0,1000,2000,3000,4000]:\n",
    "    a_x.axvline(x=i,alpha=0.7)\n",
    "    \n",
    "a_x.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(0.06,1),fontsize=18) \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "fig.savefig('Model2_d_aldakor.png')"
